<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3670309>
    dc:description "Figure 1. Known distribution of Liopeltis frenata and related taxa. Star denotes type locality. Question mark denotes and unconfirmed record of Liopeltis cf. frenata from Bhutan. Locality information. Liopeltis pallidonuchalis sp. nov.: 1 – Kon Chu Rang N.R., Gia Lai,Vietnam (type locality of Liopeltis pallidonuchalis sp. nov.; this work); 2 – Ba Na–Nui Chua N.P., Da Nang, Vietnam (as ‘Tourane’, Smith 1943); 3 – Do Quyen, Bach Ma N.P., Thua Thien–Hue, Vietnam (this work); 4 – U Bo, Phong Nha – Ke Bang N.P., Quang Binh, Vietnam (VNUH 9.7.’06–1; Ziegler et al. 2007; Luu et al. 2013); Liopeltis frenata s.str.: 5 – Khasi Hills, Meghalaya,India (restricted type locality of Cyclophis frenatus Günther,1858; Boulenger 1894; Wall 1908); 6 – Medog, Xizang, China (Zhao and Adler 1993; Zhao 2006); 7 – Mouling N.P., Arunachal Pradesh, India (Pawar and Birand 2001); 8 – Naga Hills, Nagaland, India (Ao et al. 2004); 9 – Namdapha N.P., Arunachal Pradesh, India (Pawar and Birand 2001; Krishna et al. 2012); 10 – Putao, Kachin, Myanmar (CAS 225548- 49); 11 – Htingnan, Kachin, Myanmar (Smith 1940); 12 – Myitkyina, Kachin, Myanmar (AMNH R-58541–44); 13 – Huton, Kachin Hills, Kachin, Myanmar (Wall 1925); 14 – Bhamo, Kachin, Myanmar (Smith 1943); 15 – Mansi, Kachin Hills, Kachin, Myanmar (Wall 1925); 16 – Wuliangshan Mt., Yunnan, China (this paper); 17 – Lüchun, Yunnan, China (KIZ79001; Yang and Rao 2008); 18 – Nam Xe, Van Ban, Lao Cai, Vietnam (IEBR 1205; Orlov et al. 2003); 19 – Copia N.R., Thuan Chau, Son La, Vietnam (TBU PAR.109, 116; Pham et al. 2014); 20 – Houaphan, Laos (Teynié et al. 2014); 21 – Xiangkhong, Laos (as ‘Tran-ninh’ in Smith 1943; Deuve 1970); 22 – Bo Kluea,Nan, Thailand (Hauser 2018); Liopeltis cf. stoliczkae (confirmed localities):23 – Samagooting,Nagaland,India (type locality of Ablabes stoliczkae Sclater,1891; ZSI 3955; see Das et al. 1998); 24 – Darjeeling, West Bengal, India (Smith 1943); 25 – Sikkim, India (no exact locality; Smith 1943); 26 – Karin Hills, Kayah, Myanmar (no exact locality; Smith 1943); Liopeltis cf. stoliczkae (unconfirmed localities): 27 – B La, Bao Lam, Lam Dong, Vietnam (IEBR 1293, as Liopeltis cf. tricolor; Orlov et al. 2003); 28 – Pichrada,Modolkiri,Cambodia (FMNH 259193; Stuart et al. 2006); 29 – Lac Xao, Khamkeut, Bolikhamxay, Laos (FMNH 254780; Stuart and Heatwole 2008); Doubtful localities of Liopeltis spp.in Indochina:30 – Lai Chau,Vietnam (mentioned by Hauser 2018 as Liopeltis frenata, but not" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3670309/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3670319>
    dc:description "Figure 6. Natural habitat of Liopeltis pallidonuchalis sp. nov. in Kon Chu Rang N.R., Gia Lai Province, Vietnam. Photo by Alina V. Alexandrova." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3670319/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3670321>
    dc:description "Figure 7. Morphology of Cyclophis frenatus Günther, 1858 holotype in preservative (BMNH 1946.1.1.72, male; from ‘Mountains near Affghanistan’ [= Afghanistan], corrected to ‘Khasi Hills’ by Boulenger 1894). A – general dorsal view; B – general ventral view; C – head in dorsal view; D – head in ventral view; E – head in lateral view. Photos by Gernot Vogel." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3670321/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3670323>
    dc:description "Figure 8. Liopeltis frenata (Günther, 1858) from Wuliangshan Mt., Yunnan, China, in life. (a) – general lateral view; (b) – head in lateral view. Photos by Chung-Wei You." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3670323/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

